     {q:"Why is balancing a redox equation important in chemistry?", options:["Redox equations never require any balancing","This concept has no connection to accurately representing a reaction","Balancing has no effect on the accuracy of a redox equation","It ensures the number of electrons lost equals the number of electrons gained"], answer:3}
