     {q:"Why might calorimetry be useful in fields like food science, such as determining the caloric content of food?", options:["Food science never involves measuring heat or energy content","It can measure the amount of heat energy released when a substance is broken down","This technique has no connection to measuring energy in a substance","Calorimetry has no practical application outside of a chemistry laboratory"], answer:1}
