     {q:"Why is a systematic naming system important for inorganic compounds?", options:["A systematic naming system provides no useful information about a compound","This concept only applies to purely theoretical chemistry problems","It allows chemists to communicate a compound’s exact composition clearly and consistently","Inorganic compounds have no need for a standardized naming system"], answer:2}
