     {q:"Why is it useful to review equations, trigonometry, and discrete mathematics together?", options:["It reinforces how these mathematical tools and reasoning skills connect and build on one another","Each topic must be learned in complete isolation","Review is never useful in math","These topics have no connection to each other"], answer:0}
